This makes really good use of the Fifthist lore by building on it without necessarily making the reader feel lost if they aren’t familiar with all the prior materials. Containment procedures are decent but I feel like you could’ve gotten more mileage out of them, although they do set up what comes later so if that’s all you intended it to do it’s enough. I liked that there was one incident where the Foundation basically throws up its hands, nice to be reminded they’re not infallible. I was worried the journal entries would drag on a bit but they pace themselves well and are exactly as long as they need to be. Closing addendum could’ve had more flavor but overall this really comes together well.








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






