Thank you Roget.

The way I integrated Fifthism requires a bit of author context:

+Context

-Close


I had to rewrite my first scp because it was obtuse and the GoI listed (Alexylva) was shoehorned and varied wildly from the canon (paramilitary university destroys an Atlantis founded by Aristotle followers. It's an alternate timeline where Plato reach to the light and destroys any opposing force.). I rewrote, ditching Alexylva and making more consistent elections, but I consider my worst or second worst article I ever made.




About the containment procedures, I usually like straight procedures. I think the meat is in the description and addendums.

Originally ES-105 ended at the final Celesta log, but I felt it lacked something. In a month I wrote all the journal entries and made some minor adjustments. After that, I posted it.

The final addendum is an information that they believe is related to ES-105, but also could not be. It's recent information and the Foundation tries to comprehend it







